def columns_visualozation(column):
    """ FUUNCTION:
                columns_visualization :
                        ARGUMENT : Country Name (Column_Names)
                        PROCESS  : Plots the graphs and print data of all columns as a descriptive analysis
                        RETURN   : None
                
                """
    counts = df[column].value_counts()
    percent = df[column].value_counts(normalize=True) * 100
    
    # Printing the Percentage of each type of values
    print(pd.DataFrame({"Count":counts,"Percentage":percent}).head(10))
    
    # Printing the Percentage of Nan values
    percentage_nan = df[column].isnull().sum()/(df.shape[0])*100
    print("Missing Values Percentage",percentage_nan) 
    
    values = list(df[column].value_counts().index)
    count = list(df[column].value_counts().values)

    others = sum(count[10:])
    
    # PLotting Graphs
    plt.subplots(figsize=(5,5))
    plt.barh(values[:10][::-1],count[:10][::-1],color="orange",alpha=0.7)
    plt.xlabel("COUNT")
    plt.xticks(size=14)
    plt.yticks(size=14)
    plt.ylabel("TOP 10 VALUES (Most Frequent)")
    plt.title("VALUES v/s COUNT")
    plt.grid()
    plt.show()

In [94]:
col_list=list(df)
df[col_list[1:]] = df[col_list[1:]].apply(pd.to_numeric, errors='coerce')
df['Time Serie']=pd.to_datetime(df['Time Serie'])
df_melted=df.melt(id_vars=["Time Serie"], 
        var_name="Currency type", 
        value_name="Value")
sns.set_style("white")
plt.figure(figsize=(20,10))
sns.lineplot(x="Time Serie", y="Value", hue="Currency type",palette='deep',data=df_melted)
plt.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc=2, borderaxespad=0.)

data_df = pd.read_csv('dataset.csv').copy()
data_df= data_df.replace('ND', np.nan)
data_df = data_df.dropna()
country_lst = list(data_df.columns[2:])
fig = go.Figure()
fig.update_yaxes(automargin=True)
fig.update_layout(title = 'Country Wise Comparision w.r.t USD')

for i,j in enumerate(country_lst):
    colour_lst = ['#2a850d','#91dde5','#54f1e5','#beaef4','#43142d','#7a0a8b','#04b919','#fa378c','#0bc039','#7d4c26','#2e0e88','#efd4f3','#e86f71','#d8191c','#4a31f7','#a60c7c','#dc8845','#0b92d3','#acbc09','#935049','#6cdc93','#91930b']
    fig.add_trace(
    go.Scatter(x= data_df['Time Serie'],

df = pd.read_csv('dataset.csv').copy()
df = df.replace('ND', np.nan)
df = df.fillna(method ='pad')

df = df[['Time Serie', 'UNITED KINGDOM - UNITED KINGDOM POUND/US$',
         'EURO AREA - EURO/US$' ,'SWITZERLAND - FRANC/US$', 
         'CANADA - CANADIAN DOLLAR/US$', 'CHINA - YUAN/US$', 'JAPAN - YEN/US$']]
df['Time Serie'] = pd.to_datetime(df['Time Serie'], format = '%Y-%m-%d' )
for i in [i for i in list(range(len(df.columns))) if i not in [0]]:
    df.iloc[:,i] = pd.to_numeric(df.iloc[:,i])


for column in df.drop('Time Serie', axis=1):
    df[column] = df.loc[:,column].ewm(span=30,adjust=False).mean()
    
# PLotting the graph
plt.figure(figsize=(19.2,10.8), facecolor = (0.900, 0.900, 0.900))
plt.style.use('seaborn-darkgrid')
sns.set_style("white")
# selecting color
palette = plt.get_cmap('Set1')
 
num=0
for column in df.drop('Time Serie', axis=1):
    num+=1

    plt.subplot(2,3, num)
    # plotting every groups
    for v in df.drop('Time Serie', axis=1):
        plt.plot(df['Time Serie'], df[v], marker='', color='grey', linewidth=1.2, alpha=0.8)
    #line plot
    plt.plot(df['Time Serie'], df[column], marker='', color=palette(num), linewidth=2.4, label=column)
 
    if df[column].max() < 2:
        y = 2
    else: 
        y = df[column].max() + (df[column].max() / 10)
    plt.ylim(0 ,y)
    if num in range(4) :
        plt.tick_params(labelbottom=False)
    if num not in [1,4] :
        plt.tick_params(labelleft= False)
    if num in range(4,7):
        plt.tick_params(labelleft= True)
    # Adding title
    plt.title(column, loc='left', fontsize=12, fontweight=0, color=palette(num) )
# title of the report
